            . I am the son of Patrick Sullivan - he lives in <placeName id="t18281023-241-crimeloc1403">Mary-le-bone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-241-crimeloc1403" type="placeName" value="Mary-le-bone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-241-crimeloc1403" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-241-off1401 t18281023-241-crimeloc1403"></join>. On the morning of the 15th of October, about half-past seven o'clock, I hung this coat over a broken pane of glass in the window - my mother said it was gone; I got up, and missed it - I went out and saw the prisoner and another boy doubling it up; they were a few yards off - I cried Stop thief! and went up to them; they ran different ways - the prisoner was stopped without my losing sight of him; they dropped the coat - my mother picked it up.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The other boy dropped it. Witness. Both had hold of it - I cannot say which dropped it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-241-person1270">
                  HUMPHREY 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18281023-241-person1270" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-241-person1270" type="given" value="HUMPHREY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-241-person1270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner running - he was stopped, and said no one could prove that he had the coat, and we could only give him a night's lodging.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I ran; a boy came up and said, "I'll stop you, you young rascal;" I turned round and said, "Why do you call Stop thief! after me" - they then gave charge of me.</p>
